OL,4,BHallam Amos: Cardiff and Wales wing to
OL,5,Bretire at 27 to pursue medical career
OL,6, Cardiff and Wales full-back Hallam Amos
OL,7, has announced he will retire at the end
OL,8, of the season to focus on his medical
OL,9, career.
OL,11,FAmos, 27, was left out of the Wales
OL,12,Fsquad by coach Wayne Pivac, who hinted
OL,13,Fhis medical career was a factor.
OL,15,FHe recently completed his clinical
OL,16,Fmedical exams and told Cardiff and the
OL,17,FWelsh Rugby Union (WRU) he will hang up
OL,18,Fhis boots in June 2022.
OL,20,F"This season will be my last," Amos
OL,21,Fconfirmed.
